      • nextOrderedJoinModels

        public IntList nextOrderedJoinModels()
        Optimiser may be attempting to order join clauses several times. Every time ordering takes place optimiser will keep at most two lists: one is last known order the other is new order. If new order cost is better optimiser will replace last known order with new one.

        To facilitate this behaviour the function will always return non-current list.

        Returns:
        non current order list.
